				"description": "### Get Tasks\n\nThis endpoint retrieves a list of tasks from the server. It is a simple HTTP GET request that does not require any parameters in the request body.\n\n#### Request\n\n- **Method**: GET\n    \n- **URL**: `{{baseURL}}/tasks`\n    \n\n#### Response\n\nOn a successful request, the server responds with a status code of `200` and a JSON array containing task objects. Each task object includes the following properties:\n\n- **id**: A unique identifier for the task (integer).\n    \n- **title**: The title or description of the task (string).\n    \n- **completed**: A boolean indicating whether the task has been completed.\n    \n\n#### Example Response\n\n``` json\n[\n    {\n        \"id\": 0,\n        \"title\": \"\",\n        \"completed\": true\n    }\n]\n\n ```\n\n#### Notes\n\n- The response will be an array of task objects, and the structure may vary based on the tasks stored in the database.\n    \n- Ensure that your application handles the possibility of an empty array if no tasks are available."
			},
